WEBVTT

00:01.800 --> 00:03.529
He's coming in today.
That's what I heard.

00:03.570 --> 00:05.162
Lockhart, Gardner.

00:05.200 --> 00:06.633
One second.

00:06.670 --> 00:09.434
Margie said he's coming in
for a divorce settlement.

00:09.470 --> 00:11.700
I thought he was dead.
Agos & Florrick.

00:11.740 --> 00:13.332
I'm sorry,
she's on the other line.

00:13.380 --> 00:14.677
Okay.

00:15.680 --> 00:16.669
What's Chrissy doing?

00:16.710 --> 00:18.473
Oh, you don't know, do you?

00:18.510 --> 00:20.649
When they put in the sign,
they left a hole in the wall.

00:20.680 --> 00:22.648
If you stand just right,
you can hear everything

00:22.690 --> 00:23.543
going on in the
conference room.

00:23.590 --> 00:24.784
(whispers)'
No! '

00:24.820 --> 00:26.651
(hollow tapping)

00:26.690 --> 00:28.180
(no audio)

00:31.090 --> 00:32.751
Hey, information is power.

00:41.340 --> 00:44.332
(muffled voice speaking)

00:47.540 --> 00:49.371
DAVID: Harper & Greene has this
wonderful little corner office

00:49.410 --> 00:50.377
just right for me.

00:50.410 --> 00:52.571
DIANE: Come on, David,
we go back a long ways.

00:52.620 --> 00:54.269
DAVID:
Yes, and you always had

00:54.320 --> 00:56.345
such admiration
for family law.

00:56.390 --> 00:57.539
Face it,

00:57.590 --> 00:59.581
I do my thing,
you do yours.

00:59.620 --> 01:01.349
Only difference is,
mine makes money.

01:01.390 --> 01:03.529
It's a bad economy,
David, that's all.

01:03.560 --> 01:04.720
We're righting the ship.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.193
Then right it.

01:06.230 --> 01:08.118
I have no love

01:08.160 --> 01:09.661
for this place,
but I don't want to jump

01:09.700 --> 01:11.759
to Harper & Greene
unless I have to.

01:11.800 --> 01:12.835
I don't like boxes.

01:12.870 --> 01:15.361
We're bringing in
a third partner.

01:15.400 --> 01:16.867
Yes, I've heard about
this messiah partner

01:16.910 --> 01:18.662
for two months now.
Can't wait.

01:18.710 --> 01:19.677
You could help us.

01:19.710 --> 01:21.803
Collect on overdue accounts.

01:21.840 --> 01:24.206
Yes, that's our problem.

01:27.180 --> 01:30.445
they'd bolt to another firm
before I can hang up.

01:30.490 --> 01:31.684
Give us till
the end of the week?

01:31.720 --> 01:34.757
That's what I like to hear.

01:35.820 --> 01:37.321
(door closes)

01:37.360 --> 01:39.157
We'll cull the herd.

01:42.530 --> 01:43.622
Lou...

01:43.670 --> 01:45.297
Jocelyn...

01:45.330 --> 01:47.366
Derek.

01:48.740 --> 01:50.537
And Lenny.

01:50.570 --> 01:53.277
Accounts Lenny?
Or Litigation?

01:53.310 --> 01:54.470
Litigation.

01:54.510 --> 01:56.808
That's two of yours

01:56.850 --> 01:58.670
and two of mine.

01:58.710 --> 02:00.519
And the junior associates.

02:01.850 --> 02:03.738
We have to decide now.

02:03.790 --> 02:05.746
Cary or Alicia?

02:06.960 --> 02:09.155
WILL: Friday.
We'll decide Friday.

02:09.190 --> 02:10.521
DIANE:
Good.

02:10.560 --> 02:12.699
WILL: And let's keep it
to ourselves, okay?

02:12.730 --> 02:13.549
I don't want to deal with

02:13.600 --> 02:15.693
a lot of last-minute
maneuvering on this.

02:29.810 --> 02:30.777
(knocking)

02:30.810 --> 02:32.846
Alicia. Oh.

02:32.880 --> 02:33.778
I'm sorry.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.845
Mr. Gold in my office.

02:35.880 --> 02:36.881
Again.

02:36.920 --> 02:38.785
Sorry, Alicia.
I was upstairs.

02:38.820 --> 02:41.618
And David Lee needs
to see you In ten minutes.

02:47.760 --> 02:50.320
Hey, really good
work on my brief.

02:50.370 --> 02:52.588
Thanks.
You want to_ be
a paralegal, right?

02:52.640 --> 02:53.664
Yeah, someday.

02:53.700 --> 02:55.895
All right, well,
any help you need.

03:03.780 --> 03:05.771
Cary, do you
have a minute?

03:05.810 --> 03:07.641
Sure. What's up?

03:07.680 --> 03:10.478
I just heard
something upstairs.

03:13.860 --> 03:16.681
There's a good chance
that the state's attorney

03:16.730 --> 03:17.879
won't prosecute Peter.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.952
Because of Kozko's suicide?

03:22.000 --> 03:23.888
Actually, yes.

03:23.930 --> 03:25.022
And if that does happen,

03:25.070 --> 03:28.289
you and I will have to get
on the same page quickly.

03:28.340 --> 03:29.705
What page is that?

03:29.740 --> 03:32.004
The campaign.

03:32.040 --> 03:34.679
I won't do interviews,
and I won't do photos.

03:34.710 --> 03:36.905
I know,
and I respect that.
My children won't, either.

03:36.950 --> 03:39.418
IfI could be so bold...

03:39.450 --> 03:40.712
No, you can't.

03:40.750 --> 03:42.342
Right. Got it.

03:43.550 --> 03:45.518
Anyway, that's
not why I'm here.

03:45.550 --> 03:46.812
Peter's got it
into his head

03:46.860 --> 03:48.714
that he won't run
unless you approve.

03:50.360 --> 03:52.419
I know, I tried
to convince him otherwise.

03:52.460 --> 03:55.327
I told him that wives
just get in the way, but...

03:55.360 --> 03:56.725
he's adamant.

03:56.770 --> 03:59.762
Mr. Gold, Peter is an adult.

03:59.800 --> 04:00.960
He doesn't
need a mother.

04:01.000 --> 04:02.831
We talking about you or me?

04:02.870 --> 04:03.905
(laughs)

04:03.940 --> 04:05.805
I have to get back to work.

04:05.840 --> 04:08.832
Think about it,
Mrs. Florrick.

04:08.880 --> 04:11.906
Glenn Childs is a disastrous
state's attorney.

04:11.950 --> 04:14.669
But you know that
better than I do.

04:17.990 --> 04:19.878
More kettle corn.

04:19.920 --> 04:22.059
Thank you.
This one is
bubble gum flavored.

04:22.090 --> 04:23.682
Oh, and cotton candy.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.482
Look-- separated.
I see that.

04:25.530 --> 04:27.054
Another divorce case?

04:27.100 --> 04:28.658
With a prenup.

04:28.700 --> 04:30.429
Her expectations
are too high.

04:30.470 --> 04:32.597
We have to get her down
to $300,000.

04:32.640 --> 04:34.437
Alicia, can I get
a minute with you?

04:34.470 --> 04:35.664
Regarding?

04:36.710 --> 04:39.304
That's all right.
Later.

04:41.010 --> 04:42.773
DAVID:
See? I told you.

04:42.810 --> 04:45.040
Here she is.

04:45.080 --> 04:47.674
Mrs. Caroline Wilder,
meet Alicia Florrick.

04:47.720 --> 04:48.709
Mrs. Florrick.

04:48.750 --> 04:50.445
It's really nice
to meet you.

04:50.490 --> 04:52.515
I think I'll be
turning to you

04:52.560 --> 04:53.982
for advice on how
to bounce back.

04:54.020 --> 04:56.523
But first things first--
Alicia and I

04:56.560 --> 04:58.926
were just discussing our "ask."

04:58.960 --> 05:00.052
She worries our eyes

05:00.100 --> 05:01.795
might be a little bigger
than our stomachs.

05:01.830 --> 05:03.422
Alicia.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.098
The prenup makes it
very difficult, Caroline.

05:06.130 --> 05:08.860
I was young and in love,

05:08.900 --> 05:10.800
and all of his
hit records

05:10.840 --> 05:12.102
happened before
we were married.

05:12.140 --> 05:14.836
Oh. Caroline Wilder
of Max Wilder?

05:14.880 --> 05:17.508
Oh, soon to be
ex-Max Wilder.

05:17.550 --> 05:19.916
I'm so sorry;
I didn't know.
It's okay.

05:19.950 --> 05:22.077
I'm being traded in
for a younger model.

05:22.120 --> 05:23.519
It happens.

05:23.550 --> 05:25.040
I could go to
couples therapy,

05:25.090 --> 05:27.718
I could get
a face-lift,

05:27.760 --> 05:29.955
but I can't be
28 years old again.

05:32.060 --> 05:34.494
You know the best revenge,
Caroline?

05:34.530 --> 05:36.623
I would love to know.

05:36.670 --> 05:38.023
Make him see how happy you are.

05:38.070 --> 05:39.890
(laughs softly)

05:39.940 --> 05:42.067
Let us be angry for you.

05:43.970 --> 05:46.473
CAROLINE:
Well, here comes
the parade.

05:52.010 --> 05:54.046
I thought it was just
gonna be us, Max.

05:54.080 --> 05:55.445
Oh, Shaina wanted to come.

05:55.480 --> 05:56.640
It's my right.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.442
(sighs)
Great.

05:58.490 --> 06:00.048
Love it.

06:01.620 --> 06:03.884
Okay, so, here's where we stand.

06:03.930 --> 06:05.158
DAVID:
Chocolate raisins, anyone?

06:05.190 --> 06:06.418
No, thank you.
MAX:
I will.

06:08.660 --> 06:10.093
We've reviewed
your counter--

06:10.130 --> 06:11.995
thank you for that,
by the way--

06:12.030 --> 06:13.793
and we've decided

06:13.840 --> 06:15.762
we're sticking with
our original offer.

06:15.800 --> 06:17.028
Ah. Well,

06:17.070 --> 06:20.039
that's unacceptable.
Yeah, we don't think it is.

06:20.080 --> 06:22.002
CAROLINE:
Max, after everything
we've been through,

06:22.040 --> 06:26.613
do you really believe
that $140,000 a year is fair?

06:26.650 --> 06:27.912
Well, I never thought of you

06:27.950 --> 06:29.918
as being greedy, Caroline.
Says the man

06:29.950 --> 06:31.383
with the $40 million estate.

06:35.760 --> 06:39.753
(laughs):
Look, we're not here
to argue or bandy numbers about.

06:39.800 --> 06:41.791
We've, uh, got
a court date tomorrow.

06:41.830 --> 06:44.993
Max has been more than generous
with his offer.

06:45.030 --> 06:47.430
We advise you to take it.

06:49.170 --> 06:51.604
Could you give
us a minute?

06:54.180 --> 06:57.547
Max Wilder is on probation
for a 2007 possession charge,

06:59.180 --> 07:01.512
to leave the country
this weekend.

07:02.990 --> 07:04.946
Flight reservations
to Bora-Bora.

07:04.990 --> 07:07.015
Rental of a room
to accommodate 80.

07:07.060 --> 07:08.516
They're getting married.

07:08.560 --> 07:10.528
If he makes tomorrow's
court date.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.118
How do you get
this stuff?

07:12.160 --> 07:13.559
Fnends.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.591
Just give me an
army of women.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.022
DAVID:
Sorry for that.

07:19.070 --> 07:20.958
We have your offer--

07:21.000 --> 07:23.002
thank you--

07:23.040 --> 07:25.804
and we'll just need
a few days to mull it.
Actually,

07:25.840 --> 07:27.831
no, we have
a court date tomorrow.

07:27.880 --> 07:29.973
Yes, well, why don't
we just push that off.

07:30.010 --> 07:32.149
I-I don't think
you understand.

07:32.180 --> 07:33.647
This offer came
with a clock.

07:33.680 --> 07:35.875
We need an answer now,
or we walk.

07:35.920 --> 07:37.740
Then walk.

07:38.620 --> 07:39.712
Let them go, David.

07:39.760 --> 07:40.988
Oh, Alicia,

07:41.020 --> 07:43.079
don't take out your
aggressions on this.

07:43.130 --> 07:45.553
It's insulting--
$140,000 a year.

07:46.760 --> 07:48.728
David, look,

07:48.760 --> 07:50.728
if we get an
agreement now,

07:50.770 --> 07:54.228
we can go up to $180,000,
but that exhausts our cushion.

07:54.270 --> 07:55.669
Nope, sorry.

07:55.700 --> 07:57.008
Let's take the weekend.

07:58.170 --> 07:59.706
A-Alicia, wait.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.741
Help me out with this.

08:04.780 --> 08:07.669
I want this to work.

08:11.220 --> 08:13.154
$300,000.

08:13.190 --> 08:15.078
Nicely played.
Thank you.

08:15.120 --> 08:16.781
How you doing,
Caroline?

08:16.830 --> 08:17.854
I'm fine...

08:17.890 --> 08:21.758
soon as I go home and have
a big bag of mint Milanos.

08:23.770 --> 08:26.898
(sighs) Ah, I thought I was
completely over him.

08:26.940 --> 08:29.238
Hey, John, if you could
put in a good word for me

08:29.270 --> 08:30.806
with Will and Diane.

08:30.840 --> 08:32.774
I think they're deciding
on junior associates this week.

08:32.810 --> 08:34.107
CARY:
I mean, the thing is,

08:34.140 --> 08:36.540
I like Alicia.
I think she's
doing really well,

08:36.580 --> 08:38.605
given all her problems
at home, you know?

08:38.650 --> 08:40.777
It's not really ageism
to ask how many more

08:40.820 --> 08:42.708
good working years
does anyone have left.

08:42.750 --> 08:44.638
That just makes
good sense.

08:44.690 --> 08:45.679
(chuckles)

08:45.720 --> 08:49.679
(phone ringing)

08:49.730 --> 08:51.288
(thud)

08:51.330 --> 08:52.649
Oh. Sorry, Your Honor.

08:52.700 --> 08:53.826
It's an important call.

08:53.860 --> 08:54.827
My client...

08:54.860 --> 08:55.929
Then_let me answer
It for you.

09:00.200 --> 09:02.668
Anybody else?

09:02.710 --> 09:03.961
Good.

09:04.010 --> 09:06.160
Then I understand we've
reached an agreement.

09:06.210 --> 09:07.108
Yes, Your Honor.

09:07.140 --> 09:09.643
Mrs. Wilder has acquiesced
to a divorce.

09:09.680 --> 09:11.238
We have a signed
divorce agreement.

09:11.280 --> 09:13.077
JUDGE STANEK: And Mr.
Wilder-- where is he?

09:13.120 --> 09:14.144
I'm sorry, Your Honor.

09:14.180 --> 09:16.239
My guess is that was
in fact Mr. Wilder calling.

09:16.280 --> 09:17.713
(phone vibrating)

09:17.750 --> 09:19.889
Oh. Then it's
unfortunate you didn't

09:19.920 --> 09:21.785
answer it before
court, Counselor.

09:21.820 --> 09:24.926
If I could ask for
a 30-minute recess, Your Honor,

09:24.960 --> 09:27.053
to ascertain
Mr. Wilder's whereabouts.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.897
We have no problem with that,
Your Honor.

09:28.930 --> 09:32.093
JUDGE STANEK:
Mr. Kreutzer, In my courtroom,
the people's time

09:32.130 --> 09:34.269
will be respected,
even by rock stars.

09:34.300 --> 09:36.905
You have five minutes
to locate him.

09:38.940 --> 09:40.271
JUDGE STANEK:
Five minutes!

09:49.690 --> 09:51.112
What happened?

09:51.150 --> 09:53.948
Max Wilder was just
in a motorcycle accident.

09:53.990 --> 09:56.652
Is-Is he all right?

09:56.690 --> 09:58.282
(chuckles):
No, he's in a coma.

09:58.330 --> 09:59.285
Can you believe it?

09:59.330 --> 10:00.194
Kreutzer's gonna have a fit.

10:00.230 --> 10:02.118
Yes, Margie...
Shh, shh, shh, just listen.

10:02.160 --> 10:04.162
You made notes
on the Wilder prenup.

10:04.200 --> 10:07.067
What does it say
on power of attorney?

10:07.100 --> 10:08.135
She could get half.

10:08.170 --> 10:11.162
Yep. If he stays in a coma,
$40 million estate.

10:11.210 --> 10:12.700
Margie, you're killing me.

10:14.880 --> 10:16.233
We need to tell her.

10:16.280 --> 10:18.942
No, no, no. We need to
make her filthy rich first.

10:18.980 --> 10:21.210
Margie, now!

10:22.280 --> 10:23.884
We're good.
We're good.

10:35.160 --> 10:37.060
What did you do?
Your Honor,

10:37.100 --> 10:39.318
we already have
a divorce agreement.

10:39.370 --> 10:41.338
It's not signed. We don't have
a properly signed...

10:41.370 --> 10:43.361
'Cause you took a page!
Stop it, the both of you.

10:43.410 --> 10:45.162
JUDGE STANEK:
Where's Mr. Wilder?

10:45.210 --> 10:47.007
KREUTZER:
He was in an accident,
Your Honor.

10:47.040 --> 10:48.735
He's in a coma, but
this divorce is done.

10:48.780 --> 10:51.203
Your Honor, in our rush
to get to the court on time,

10:51.250 --> 10:52.672
I'm afraid we may
have overlooked

10:52.720 --> 10:56.110
the very last page
of the divorce agreement.

10:56.150 --> 10:57.287
KREUTZER:
David, come on!

10:57.320 --> 10:58.309
JUDGE STANEK:
Stop it!

11:03.790 --> 11:07.692
Captioning sponsored by
CBS TELEVISION

11:18.470 --> 11:20.938
DAVID:
You don't understand.

11:20.980 --> 11:23.801
This just turned into
a $40 million divorce.

11:23.850 --> 11:25.169
No, it's just me and Alicia.

11:25.210 --> 11:26.711
I need troops.

11:26.750 --> 11:29.139
On their way,
and I'll take litigation.

11:29.180 --> 11:32.149
(sighs)

11:32.190 --> 11:34.158
Max Wilder was just
in a motorcycle accident.

11:34.190 --> 11:35.748
He's in a coma.

11:35.790 --> 11:37.223
You're kidding.
No.

11:37.260 --> 11:41.321
And our client controls
his $40 million estate

11:41.360 --> 11:43.021
if he stays in a coma.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.220
(whistles)
Here's the rub.

11:45.270 --> 11:47.067
David's looking at the will.

11:47.100 --> 11:48.988
Our guess is
he wrote our client out.

11:49.040 --> 11:51.065
So if he dies...
She gets nothing.

11:51.110 --> 11:52.008
Just the prenup.

11:52.040 --> 11:55.931
So we're cheering for him
to stay in a coma?

11:55.980 --> 11:57.402
Effectively.

11:57.450 --> 11:57.905
(sighs)

11:57.950 --> 11:58.609
We're like ghouls.

11:58.650 --> 12:00.709
As long as we're solvent ghouls.

12:02.080 --> 12:03.445
(sighs)

12:03.490 --> 12:06.755
Oh, uh, what do you think
of Vernon Jordan?

12:06.790 --> 12:09.258
What do I think
of Vernon Jordan?
Yes.

12:09.290 --> 12:10.780
As a third partner.

12:10.830 --> 12:13.151
Oh. I...

12:13.200 --> 12:14.394
Is that a possibility?

12:14.430 --> 12:16.091
He's been sniffing around us,

12:16.130 --> 12:17.995
looking for an opening
into Chicago.

12:18.030 --> 12:19.793
Well, that
would be...
A lifesaver.

12:19.840 --> 12:21.967
We wouldn't have
to make cuts.

12:22.000 --> 12:24.059
I'll try to set up a meeting.

12:24.110 --> 12:26.328
CARY: I'll take any
support I can get.
Uh, Cary?

12:27.380 --> 12:30.144
I need you on the
Wilder divorce.

12:30.180 --> 12:31.772
It suddenly became important.

12:31.810 --> 12:33.414
Yeah, yeah, sure, sure.
Anything.

12:33.450 --> 12:35.042
I'll head off
right away.

12:38.190 --> 12:40.215
I didn't say anything.

12:40.260 --> 12:43.149
(footsteps approaching)

12:45.560 --> 12:47.949
Oh, my God.

12:48.000 --> 12:49.968
Hey.

12:50.000 --> 12:52.025
(sniffles)

12:52.070 --> 12:54.891
They say he just swerved
into oncoming traffic.

12:54.940 --> 12:57.829
I always hated
that thing.

12:57.870 --> 13:00.304
Alicia, this is
Jay Van Zandt.
Hi.

13:00.340 --> 13:02.399
CAROLINE:
Max's manager.

13:02.440 --> 13:03.998
Alicia's my lavwer.

13:04.050 --> 13:05.199
(sighs)

13:05.250 --> 13:06.547
I don't know.

13:06.580 --> 13:08.047
Maybe I shouldn't
be here.

13:08.080 --> 13:11.243
He talked about you, Caroline,
just last week.

13:11.290 --> 13:12.985
No, he didn't.

13:13.020 --> 13:14.988
Don't try
to make me feel better.

13:17.090 --> 13:18.887
He looks so 5...

13:18.930 --> 13:21.091
DAVID:
3.4 million in Kauai.

13:21.130 --> 13:24.019
5.5 million of the
properties in Chicago.

13:24.070 --> 13:25.526
You can't use your
cell phone in here.

13:25.570 --> 13:27.037
You know
that's a myth, right?

13:27.070 --> 13:29.288
Where's the doctor?
He's in with
Mrs. Wilder.

13:29.340 --> 13:31.160
DAVID:
Mrs...?!

13:34.940 --> 13:36.999
The helmet protected the
frontal and temporal bone,

13:37.050 --> 13:38.540
but the base of the
helmet snapped back,

13:38.580 --> 13:40.514
causing severe trauma
to the cerebellum.

13:40.550 --> 13:42.939
We've stopped
the bleeding, but...

13:42.990 --> 13:44.116
I'm sorry.

13:44.150 --> 13:45.617
It's a subdural hematoma.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.515
Which means...?

13:47.560 --> 13:49.926
Mrs. Wilder, your husband
is effectively brain dead.

