30:02.360 --> 30:05.158
What kind of timeline
are we talking here?
Fnday.

30:05.200 --> 30:06.963
Fnday?!

30:07.000 --> 30:08.934
For a call or...?

30:08.970 --> 30:10.369
This was stupid.
I'm sorry, Mr. Gold. I...

30:10.400 --> 30:12.402
No, Alicia, stop.

30:12.440 --> 30:14.408
What's going on?

30:14.440 --> 30:15.600
Talk to me.

30:15.640 --> 30:16.902
No, it's my own thing.

30:16.940 --> 30:18.874
No, it's not
your own thing.

30:18.910 --> 30:21.174
I know I don't seem like the
warm and understanding type,

30:21.220 --> 30:24.189
but this is my warm
and understanding face.

30:26.590 --> 30:29.411
I'm in competition with
another junior associate.

30:29.460 --> 30:30.256
And?

30:32.560 --> 30:35.597
You're worried
you're gonna get laId off.

30:35.630 --> 30:37.154
Okay, I can hire

30:37.200 --> 30:39.122
the guy away,
and then dump him.

30:39.170 --> 30:40.967
No, no.
No, I do it all the time.

30:41.000 --> 30:43.195
Just offer them massive salary,
and then when they get here--

30:43.240 --> 30:44.229
Oop, the position's gone.

30:44.270 --> 30:45.430
No, please.

30:45.470 --> 30:49.577
Uh... It was wrong
for me to come here.

30:49.610 --> 30:51.077
I don't want
to do this.

30:51.110 --> 30:53.169
I'm not this person.

30:53.210 --> 30:56.043
Mrs. Florrick,
ifI know one thing in life,

30:56.080 --> 30:58.048
it's that everybody
is that person.

30:59.990 --> 31:01.958
Let me make a few calls, okay?

31:01.990 --> 31:03.514
Fnday?

31:06.190 --> 31:08.090
Hey, I'm just making the calls.

31:08.130 --> 31:10.052
You get the client,
it's your client,

31:10.100 --> 31:12.068
Okay?

31:15.170 --> 31:16.637
Thank you.

31:16.670 --> 31:19.104
Hey, we're like
family, right?

31:27.010 --> 31:29.979
CAROLINE:
I guess I can't let go.

31:31.520 --> 31:33.988
When Max and I were in rehab...

31:36.190 --> 31:40.149
...there was this 12-step quote
we used to say,

31:40.190 --> 31:42.988
(voice breaking): "Don't quit
before the miracle happens."

31:45.400 --> 31:47.197
And they say
that it's a million-to-one shot,

31:47.230 --> 31:51.269
but Max's life,

31:51.310 --> 31:55.599
becoming who he was...

31:55.640 --> 31:59.246
that was
a million-to-one shot.

32:02.450 --> 32:04.918
Max loved life.

32:06.390 --> 32:09.109
He loved action.

32:11.090 --> 32:15.049
He was going to slqdive
on his 80th birthday.

32:15.100 --> 32:18.092
So I know for a fact

32:18.130 --> 32:20.223
that he would never want this.

32:24.640 --> 32:27.200
(voice breaking):
I'm sorry,

32:27.240 --> 32:30.129
but he's gone.

32:32.710 --> 32:34.018
Caroline...

32:35.550 --> 32:38.246
I know we both love him,

32:38.290 --> 32:40.542
but he's...

32:43.360 --> 32:47.057
This is torturing him.

32:49.760 --> 32:52.092
(rhythm and blues playing)

32:59.370 --> 33:01.031
Is that the tox report?

33:01.080 --> 33:03.230
Yep.
Hmm.

33:03.280 --> 33:05.145
You're not going to let
me see it, are you?

33:05.180 --> 33:07.148
I'm thinking about it.

33:10.050 --> 33:11.540
(clears throat)

33:11.590 --> 33:14.115
I had him checked
for drugs and alcohol.

33:14.160 --> 33:15.252
But they already...

33:15.290 --> 33:16.211
When they didn't
find anything,

33:16.260 --> 33:18.558
I had them check for
other foreign substances.

33:18.590 --> 33:21.354
Mr. Wilder ingested
ethylene glycol.

33:21.400 --> 33:23.322
Antifreeze.

33:23.360 --> 33:26.158
That's why
the drunken appearance.

33:26.200 --> 33:28.361
We're opening up
a murder investigation

33:28.400 --> 33:29.765
with your client
as the prime suspect.

33:29.800 --> 33:32.360
Why?

33:32.410 --> 33:35.231
A $40 million motive,
for one thing.

33:35.280 --> 33:36.406
Great.

33:37.540 --> 33:38.677
Where's the rest?

33:40.310 --> 33:42.540
Why aren't you
answering my calls?

33:42.580 --> 33:45.083
Because I'm in a relationship.

33:45.120 --> 33:47.042
I don't believe you.
Believe me.

33:47.090 --> 33:49.411
Not with that kiss.

33:51.390 --> 33:55.326
Look, I know you have
vulnerability issues.

33:55.360 --> 33:56.554
(scoffs)

33:56.600 --> 33:58.568
I don't want
to cuddle with you.

33:58.600 --> 34:00.329
Ijust...

34:10.310 --> 34:12.346
That's all.

34:12.380 --> 34:14.541
Purely recreational.

34:14.580 --> 34:18.118
You go to somebody else
for emotional validation.

34:22.220 --> 34:24.256
Drink your drink,
pay the bill,

34:24.290 --> 34:26.679
then follow me out.

34:51.850 --> 34:55.308
DAVID:
Toxicology report pinpoints
the poisoning as happening

34:55.360 --> 34:56.588
between 10:00 am.
and noon,

34:56.620 --> 34:58.429
when Max
was at the house.

34:58.460 --> 35:01.395
CAROLINE:
But I wasn't at
Max's house.

35:01.430 --> 35:03.159
Do you have any proof?

35:03.200 --> 35:05.191
That was just before
you went to court.

35:05.230 --> 35:07.391
I don't know.
I mean, I-I guess so.

35:07.430 --> 35:09.136
I'm trying to think.

35:09.170 --> 35:11.309
ALICIA:
The police believe they've
established motive, Caroline.

35:11.340 --> 35:12.762
Now they're trying
to establish access

35:12.810 --> 35:14.300
by putting you
at the house.

35:14.340 --> 35:15.739
Could Shaina
have been there?

35:15.780 --> 35:17.475
Yeah, I mean, she has a key,

35:17.510 --> 35:18.408
so I guess it's possible.

35:18.450 --> 35:21.613
Do you really think
that they suspect me?

35:21.650 --> 35:23.413
Yeah.

35:25.920 --> 35:26.909
KALIN DA:
Who's that?

35:26.950 --> 35:29.555
It's our savior.

35:30.820 --> 35:31.821
So, Mr. Jordan...

35:31.860 --> 35:33.851
Vernon, please.

35:33.890 --> 35:36.893
So, Vernon, you've been
looking us over, I hear.

35:36.930 --> 35:39.228
That's right.
I love Chicago.

35:39.270 --> 35:42.194
Summers of '57, '58,
I drove the city bus.

35:42.240 --> 35:43.491
(laughs):
Really?

35:43.540 --> 35:44.939
WILL:
Best buses in the world.

35:44.970 --> 35:47.803
My first
big city experience.

35:47.840 --> 35:51.742
Well, I don't think
we'd be speaking out of turn

35:51.780 --> 35:54.510
to say we're happy
to be looked over.

35:54.550 --> 35:57.872
We're hoping you can
open some doors for
us to Washington.

35:57.920 --> 35:59.888
Well, it's a new economy.

35:59.920 --> 36:01.808
We all have to diversify.

36:01.860 --> 36:04.681
So after your tire-kicking,
what do you think, Vernon?

36:04.730 --> 36:07.824
I think the firm
lacks focus.

36:07.860 --> 36:10.954
It seems as if you're
taking cases on a whim.

36:11.000 --> 36:12.763
I think you've nailed
our vulnerability.

36:12.800 --> 36:15.689
More passion sometimes
than sense.

36:15.740 --> 36:17.765
Will and I know that

36:17.800 --> 36:19.358
we need a referee.

36:19.410 --> 36:21.605
So we would be willing
to offer a three-way split.

36:22.640 --> 36:25.541
I-I'm sorry, I thought...

36:25.580 --> 36:27.468
I want to buy you out.

36:30.550 --> 36:33.212
Is that not what you want?

36:39.690 --> 36:41.794
Well, that didn't go well.

36:41.830 --> 36:43.388
Who would have thought

36:43.430 --> 36:45.864
_our firm means more
WIthout us than WIth us?

36:47.000 --> 36:50.197
Really undercuts
one's conﬁdence.

36:52.940 --> 36:54.305
Well...

36:54.340 --> 36:57.229
it's time to make
some tough deCISIons.

37:05.750 --> 37:07.684
(ringtone playing on video)

37:11.730 --> 37:14.722
(ringtone continues)

37:15.860 --> 37:17.657
(ringtone stops)

37:17.700 --> 37:18.826
TONY:
And you weren't here?

37:18.870 --> 37:20.019
No.

37:20.070 --> 37:22.891
You never went
to hIs house?

37:22.940 --> 37:24.305
That day? No.

37:24.340 --> 37:26.501
Who has keys to his house?

37:26.540 --> 37:28.735
Well, I'm not
completely sure.

37:28.780 --> 37:30.338
Jay?

37:30.380 --> 37:32.598
Uh, as far
as I remember,

37:32.650 --> 37:35.016
Max, Shaina
and the housekeeper.

37:35.050 --> 37:36.870
And Mrs. Wilder, too?

37:36.920 --> 37:38.478
Well, yes.

37:38.520 --> 37:40.511
When was the last time
you saw Max?

37:40.550 --> 37:42.518
JAY:
Uh, the night before.

37:42.560 --> 37:45.028
And he seemed
in a good mood, you know.

37:45.060 --> 37:46.357
Um, looking forward
to his wedding.

37:46.390 --> 37:47.926
Can I have his
business card.

37:47.960 --> 37:49.097
Whose?
HIs.

37:49.130 --> 37:51.519
Why?
TONY:
The housekeeper--
what are her hours?

37:51.570 --> 37:52.969
JAY:
I don't know.

37:53.000 --> 37:54.490
I could get
her number for you.

37:54.540 --> 37:56.565
Max would just let anybody in?

37:56.600 --> 37:57.965
Yes.

37:58.000 --> 38:02.039
(ringtone playing loudly)

38:02.080 --> 38:04.469
Oh, sorry, sorry.

38:05.750 --> 38:07.809
Hello.

38:07.850 --> 38:10.011
Hello.

38:14.460 --> 38:16.451
So we're all set.

38:16.490 --> 38:18.629
My client receives a
million a year for life.

38:18.660 --> 38:20.480
My client gets
the rest of the estate,

38:20.530 --> 38:21.895
and full guardianship.

38:21.930 --> 38:23.488
Of a comatose patient.

38:23.530 --> 38:24.895
It's what she wants.

38:24.930 --> 38:27.069
So you're the reason
Jay did it.

38:27.100 --> 38:29.034
Well, I'm not the reason,

38:29.070 --> 38:32.039
but Max and Shaina were
plannIng to change the WIN

38:32.070 --> 38:33.435
after they got married.

38:33.470 --> 38:35.529
Shaina wanted
to remove Jay.

38:35.580 --> 38:38.674
Ah, money. Dependable money.

38:38.710 --> 38:40.507
Pleasure doing business
with you.
You, too.

38:41.950 --> 38:43.110
Alicia, Cary.

38:43.150 --> 38:45.311
Will and Diane
want to see you.

38:48.120 --> 38:49.758
Thank you, Courtney.
We'll be right up.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.729
It's weird, huh?

38:56.760 --> 39:00.025
It's like a date
with the executioner.

39:00.070 --> 39:02.459
Nice working with you.

39:02.500 --> 39:03.592
You, too.

39:03.640 --> 39:05.062
You're a good lawyer.

39:17.880 --> 39:20.440
Do you know what you'll do
if it goes against you?

39:20.490 --> 39:21.559
No.

39:21.590 --> 39:22.682
You?

39:22.720 --> 39:23.914
No idea.

39:23.960 --> 39:28.727
I hear it's always
the first one called in.

39:28.760 --> 39:30.421
They're the one
who gets fired.

39:30.460 --> 39:32.098
I really didn't
need to know that.

39:32.130 --> 39:33.995
Sorry.

39:55.160 --> 39:58.084
My clients kept asking,
ifI was so high

39:58.120 --> 40:00.725
on your firm, why wasn't
I bringing my business here?

40:00.760 --> 40:03.524
And I didn't want to
appear hypocritical.

40:03.560 --> 40:05.164
Mr. Gold...

40:05.200 --> 40:06.167
Eli.

40:06.200 --> 40:09.067
Eli, you...

40:09.100 --> 40:10.590
Thank you.

40:10.640 --> 40:13.404
And, hey,
I hear it's a good firm.

40:14.580 --> 40:16.138
And we'll have to talk.

40:16.180 --> 40:18.000
About?

40:18.040 --> 40:20.645
Your husband's campaign.

40:30.120 --> 40:31.849
(door opening)

40:33.130 --> 40:35.189
Alicia, would you
come in, please?

40:45.740 --> 40:47.139
(lock clicks)

40:51.080 --> 40:54.675
We don't mean to draw this out
any longer than we have to.

40:56.250 --> 40:57.740
Good job, Alicia.

40:57.780 --> 40:59.589
WILL:
Very good job.

40:59.620 --> 41:01.144
(sighs)

41:01.190 --> 41:03.078
Thanks for going
all-out this year.
It's been quite a ride.

41:03.120 --> 41:05.122
DIANE:
And we're not out
of the woods yet.

41:05.160 --> 41:06.627
We have a lot of trimming to do,

41:06.660 --> 41:08.218
so we're all going to have
to work harder.

41:08.260 --> 41:10.057
WILL:
Do more with less.
I'm ready.

41:10.100 --> 41:11.590
DIANE:
We know you are,

41:11.630 --> 41:13.120
and, uh, thanks for
listening the other day.

41:13.170 --> 41:14.990
You heard us.

41:15.040 --> 41:16.268
That's all we needed to know.

41:16.300 --> 41:19.064
No; thank you.

41:38.790 --> 41:39.927
You okay?

41:39.960 --> 41:42.258
Yes.

41:42.300 --> 41:44.666
Don't worry,
everything's gonna be fine.

41:46.700 --> 41:48.759
Cary, do you
have a minute?

41:48.800 --> 41:50.665
Yes.

42:06.120 --> 42:08.088
We're sorry.

42:09.820 --> 42:13.028
DIANE:
You were great, Cary.

42:13.060 --> 42:15.051
And if we weren't
in this situation--

42:15.100 --> 42:18.592
this financial situation--
we would want you both.

42:18.630 --> 42:19.597
I understand.

42:19.630 --> 42:21.939
We can make a few calls
for you, if you'd like.

42:21.970 --> 42:25.906
And we would give you
unqualified references.
Thank you.

42:28.310 --> 42:30.198
Do you have any questions?

42:30.240 --> 42:33.175
No. I get it.

